==English==

===Etymology===
Latin ''[[vesica#Latin|vesica]]'' ‘bladder’.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/'vɛsɪkə/}}, {{IPA|/'vi:sɪkə/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|vesic|ae}}

# {{anatomy}} A [[bladder]], especially the [[urinary bladder]] or the [[gall bladder]].
# the [[vesica piscis]] or oval aureole in mediaeval painting
#:*'''1862''': This figure is surrounded by a double border of golden rays following the same '''vesica''' outline, behind which the background is dispersed with starry circles. — ''The Times'', 30 Aug 1862, p.10 col. F

